<div class='commentinfo comment_comment'>
2011-05-04 11:05:14 (1123 days ago)
<div id='contact-10264'><span class='name'>Phillip Merica II</span><span class='send-message'><a href="/content/Contact/view/contactid/10264/display/detail/">Details</a></span></div> </div>
<div class='commentbox'>
D-Lowe and I ran this Sat. 4-16 after alot of rain. I would say it was med-high level and Very<br/>
continuous. I would give it a 4+ at this level due to the lack of eddie service, almost none. Most<br/>
all of the wood was avoidable in one way or another. Would be nice to see again after some wood<br/>
removal. I called it after about a mile or so due to a busted boat and shoulder. It is a little<br/>
abusive for us open-boaters, though I think it may have been a first OC1 descent. Overall,Very<br/>
Narrow, Fast and Continuous. Think I'll let it simmer down a bit next time. Flip </div>
</td>
</tr>
